summary:
The Security Council:
- Requests the Secretary-General to update on the deployment of UN civilian police;
- Reiterates support for the Special Court for Sierra Leone, encourages donations to the Trust Fund, and urges UNAMSIL to provide support;
- Welcomes progress on the Truth and Reconciliation Commission and urges donors to commit funds;
- Encourages the Mano River Union Presidents to continue dialogue and implement regional peace and security commitments;
- Welcomes efforts to solve the Liberia conflict, demands refraining from illegal incursions into Sierra Leone, and calls for embargo compliance;
- Encourages the Government of Sierra Leone to address the needs of women and children;
- Welcomes steps to prevent sexual abuse and exploitation by UNAMSIL and calls for zero tolerance;
- Encourages support for refugee and displaced person returns;
- Welcomes the Secretary-General's intention to monitor the situation and report to the Council;
- Decides to remain seized of the matter.
